  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed (all achieving required levels under the Minimal profile thresholds) and six factors were scoped out as not applicable to the narrow hemolysis QoI evaluated here. The intended use scope — steady-state, single operating point (6 L/min, 120 mmHg, 3600 RPM), in-vitro bovine blood analogue — is documented in the Claim and Requirement nodes bound below. Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-vad-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-velocity-dataset-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-invitro-bovine-2022"
  ],
